      "text": "A 32-year-old male presents with a lifelong pattern of social withdrawal. He avoids social interactions, prefers to be alone, and shows no interest in forming close relationships. He appears emotionally distant and indifferent to praise or criticism. On examination, there are no signs of psychosis, delusions, or hallucinations. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Schizotypal Personality Disorder",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Schizoid Personality Disorder",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Paranoid Personality Disorder",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Avoidant Personality Disorder",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "B. Schizoid Personality Disorder",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table align=\"center\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:625px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Disorder</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Diagnosis</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Treatment</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Paranoid Personality Disorder </strong><strong>(Option C ruled out)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Pervasive distrust and suspiciousness of others</li>\n<li>Hostility, irritability, anger</li>\n<li>Difficulty with trust and intimacy</li>\n<li>Cynical view of world</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>No fixed delusions (vs. delusional disorder)</li>\n<li>No hallucinations or formal thought disorder (vs. schizophrenia)</li>\n<li>No tumultuous relationships (vs. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2d896c605a1692777183d769916056\">borderline</span> personality disorder)</li>\n<li>No history of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6133b1827c16927771813719d533eb\">antisocial</span> behavior (vs. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6133b1827c16927771813719d533eb\">antisocial</span> personality disorder)</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Psychotherapy</strong>: Straightforward and honest therapist, avoid warmth or deep interpretation</li>\n<li><strong>Group therapy</strong>: Helpful for some, but poorly tolerated</li>\n<li><strong>Behavior therapy</strong>: Social skills training, may feel intrusive</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Schizoid Personality Disorder </strong><strong>(Option B)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Lifelong social withdrawal</li>\n<li>Eccentric, isolated, and lonely</li>\n<li>Introverted with a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"862b9b46641692777183ea602de834\">bland</span> affect</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>No <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"23702653681692777196e5c0fc63cd\">psychotic</span> symptoms (vs. schizophrenia, delusional disorder)</li>\n<li>More withdrawn and aloof (vs. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"39a55021ff16927771946d220fe0db\">paranoid</span> personality disorder)</li>\n<li>No dysphoric loneliness</li>\n<li>Fewer past relationships, possible <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"23691f29951692777182c8a175f8da\">autistic</span> reverie</li>\n<li><strong>No desire for social interaction (vs. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"240194a57e1692777182d93c2587cd\">avoidant</span> personality disorder)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Psychotherapy</strong>: Build trust, encourage expression</li>\n<li><strong>Group therapy</strong>: May benefit, initial silence likely</li>\n<li><strong>Pharmacotherapy</strong>: Limited evidence, medications for specific symptoms (e.g., emotional detachment)</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Schizotypal Personality Disorder </strong><strong>(Option A ruled out)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Social difficulties</li>\n<li>Eccentric behavior and thinking (\u201cmagical thinking\u201d)</li>\n<li>Peculiar speech, superstitious beliefs, perceptual illusions</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Odd behavior, thinking, and perception (vs. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5638d8858f1692777198a97a561a88\">schizoid</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"240194a57e1692777182d93c2587cd\">avoidant</span> personality disorders)</li>\n<li>Differentiated from <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"59f989084e16927771822f692979f5\">autism</span> by the severity of language disorder</li>\n<li>Lacks psychosis, or it's brief (vs. schizophrenia)</li>\n<li>No odd behavior (vs. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"39a55021ff16927771946d220fe0db\">paranoid</span> personality disorder)</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Psychotherapy</strong>: Sensitive approach to avoid ridicule</li>\n<li><strong>Antipsychotics</strong>: Manage illusions and odd ideas</li>\n<li><strong>Antidepressants</strong>: Used for depressive symptoms</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Disorder</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Diagnosis Criteria</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Treatment</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Paranoid Personality Disorder</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Distrust, hostility, and suspicion</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">No delusions, hallucinations, or tumultuous relationships</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Psychotherapy, group therapy, behavior therapy</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Schizoid Personality Disorder</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Social withdrawal, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"897ef2d27c16927771861eb7f4726c\">eccentric</span> behavior</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Absence of psychosis; does not desire social interaction</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Psychotherapy, group therapy, limited pharmacotherapy</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Schizotypal Personality Disorder</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Eccentric behavior, perceptual oddities</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Odd thinking, perceptual illusions, no psychosis</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Psychotherapy, antipsychotics, antidepressants</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
