      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table align=\"center\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:624px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Cluster C Personality Disorders</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Characteristics</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Diagnosis</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Treatment</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Avoidant/ Anxious Personality Disorder</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hypersensitivity to rejection</strong></li>\n<li>Desires close relationships but avoids them due to fear of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"49e378f9f71692777197bc5e458569\">rejection</span> or criticism</li>\n<li>Timid and lacks self-confidence</li>\n<li>Misinterprets others\u2019 comments negatively</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Differentiate from:</li>\n<li><strong>Social Anxiety Disorder:</strong> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d61e782bf41692777182f829eef312\">Avoidance</span> of specific situations</li>\n<li><strong>Panic Disorder with Agoraphobia:</strong> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d61e782bf41692777182f829eef312\">Avoidance</span> develops after panic attacks</li>\n<li><strong>Schizoid Personality Disorder:</strong> Desires social interaction unlike those with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5638d8858f1692777198a97a561a88\">schizoid</span> disorder.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Psychotherapy:</strong></li>\n<li>Build a strong <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8dfaeedbf91692777200561b2b1d2f\">therapeutic</span> alliance</li>\n<li>Encourage gradual risk-taking in social situations</li>\n<li>Group therapy for understanding social fears</li>\n<li>Assertiveness training for better self-expression and self-esteem</li>\n<li><strong>Pharmacotherapy:</strong></li>\n<li>Beta-adrenergic antagonists like atenolol</li>\n<li>Serotonergic agents like SSRI</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Dependent Personality Disorder </strong><strong>(Option A ruled out)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Pervasive dependent and submissive behavior</strong></li>\n<li>Difficulty making decisions without reassurance</li>\n<li>Avoids responsibility</li>\n<li>Fears being alone; may tolerate abusive relationships for connection</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Differentiate from:</li>\n<li><strong>Histrionic Personality Disorder:</strong> More manipulative and often involved in short-term relationships</li>\n<li><strong>Borderline Personality Disorder:</strong> More unstable relationships.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Psychotherapy:</strong> Insight oriented therapy, behavior therapy, assertiveness training, family therapy and group therapy are also found useful.</li>\n<li><strong>Pharmacotherapy:</strong> Symptomatic management such as antidepressants.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Obsessive- Compulsive Personality Disorder </strong><strong>(Option C ruled out)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Preoccupation with orderliness, perfectionism, and control</strong></li>\n<li>Rigid and inflexible</li>\n<li>Difficulty relaxing</li>\n<li>Highly devoted to work, often neglecting relationships</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Differentiate from:</li>\n<li><strong>Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder (OCD):</strong> Symptoms are less severe and time-consuming in OCPD.</li>\n<li>Ego- syntonic in OCPD vs ego- dystonic in OCD</li>\n<li>Diagnosis is reserved for those with significant occupational or social impairment.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Psychotherapy:</strong></li>\n<li>Cognitive therapy or cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT)</li>\n<li>Interpersonal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f3f884992516927771965b324c2faf\">psychotherapy</span> may help with depressive symptoms</li>\n<li><strong>Pharmacotherapy:</strong> Limited evidence; some studies suggest benefits from <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"05412e7b9e1692777203c62877cb64\">fluvoxamine</span> and carbamazepine. Citalopram may help with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"843b8ecd5416927771842bc110b4e3\">comorbid</span> depression.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
