    {
      "text": "A 30-year-old male presents with episodes of sudden aggression, leading to property destruction and physical assaults. He reports feeling intense tension before these outbursts and experiences significant guilt and remorse afterward. Which of the following impulse control disorders is most likely affecting him?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Kleptomania",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Pyromania",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Intermittent Explosive Disorder",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Compulsive Hoarding",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "C. Intermittent Explosive Disorder",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table align=\"center\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:614px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Disorder</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Description</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Intermittent <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"dd9858c0bf1692777187ed886e9735\">Explosive</span> Disorder </strong><strong>(Option C)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Episodes of uncontrolled aggression leading to assaults or property damage.</li>\n<li>Aggression is disproportionate to triggers; episodes are followed by regret.</li>\n<li>Important to rule out other causes.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Kleptomania </strong><strong>(Option A ruled out)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Recurring urge to steal unnecessary items, with gratification derived from the act.</li>\n<li>Guilt or anxiety may follow, but not anger or revenge.</li>\n<li>Most shoplifters do not have kleptomania.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Pyromania </strong><strong>(Option B\u00a0ruled out)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Repeated deliberate fire-setting, accompanied by an urge and a sense of relief.</li>\n<li>Individuals may show no remorse or concern for consequences.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table align=\"center\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:614px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Disorder</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Common <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"843b8ecd5416927771842bc110b4e3\">Comorbid</span> Conditions</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Intermittent <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"dd9858c0bf1692777187ed886e9735\">Explosive</span> Disorder</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Often co-occurs with substance use disorders, mood disorders, anxiety disorders, personality disorders, PTSD, and eating disorders.</li>\n<li>Increased risk of self-harm.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Kleptomania</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Frequently <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"843b8ecd5416927771842bc110b4e3\">comorbid</span> with major depressive disorder, anxiety disorders, other impulse control disorders, eating disorders, personality disorders, OCD, and substance use disorders.</li>\n<li>Increased suicide risk.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Pyromania</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Often associated with substance use disorders, mood disorders (depressive and bipolar), and other impulse control disorders.</li>\n<li>Increased suicidal thoughts reported.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table align=\"center\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:614px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Disorder</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Recommended Treatments</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Intermittent <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"dd9858c0bf1692777187ed886e9735\">Explosive</span> Disorder</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Focus on recognizing warning signs and developing <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"115f40291e16927771851b4fbf5940\">coping</span> mechanisms.</li>\n<li>Effective therapies include CBT and family therapy.</li>\n<li>Medications: anticonvulsants, lithium, SSRIs.</li>\n<li>Best chances of success: combination of medication and psychotherapy.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Kleptomania</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Insight-oriented psychotherapy, psychoanalysis, CBT, and behavioral therapies (e.g., <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"686725cf89169277719994d7d523d1\">systematic</span> desensitization).</li>\n<li>Medications: SSRIs, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"66bf14385516927772001b3646b855\">tricyclic</span> antidepressants, lithium, naltrexone.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Pyromania</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Treatment is challenging; CBT is the most promising approach.</li>\n<li>Family therapy is essential for youth.</li>\n<li>Limited medication options; potential benefits from SSRIs, lithium, naltrexone.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
